<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-30T23:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-30T23:30:00-05:00" n="388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">846E.2395/7–3151: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ceylon</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Satterthwaite</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colombo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-31T10:00:00+05:30">July
                                        31, 1951—10 a. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>61. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 60, July 31. Embassy
                                considers leak most unfortunate because possible disrupting effect
                                on market and particularly because contemplated contract (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1, July 2) wld fall so far
                                short of expectation created by daily news articles that general
                                dissatisfaction locally inevitable. Embassy anticipates glut of
                                inquiries and will continue deny all knowledge until instructed
                                otherwise.</p>
                            <p>Dept pass London; sent Dept 61, rptd info London 13.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Satterthwaite</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>